      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DOUBLE IT HARRY (4) had been racing very well in NSW and continued that form at Redcliffe last week, leading and digging deep to get home narrowly. Draws a little wider but can still push forward. Has winning claims again. ALWAYS BE CHAPS (10) cops a tricky barrier but the form is hard to knock. Chased a good one when runner-up last time after winning his first two runs off a spell, one from a similar barrier. Threat with even luck. SHEZ SWEET LOUISE NZ (2) drew wide and chased a Group 1 winner when resuming last week but she is much better served by this draw and she goes well second up with a win and a placing from two attempts. Expect big improvement. BETTERTHAN POPSY (1) has trialled since coming from this barrier for a close second at his most recent appearance at Redcliffe. Can be competitive.",
